The 80th Annual Confer­ence of the United Afri­can Methodist Church (UAMC) Worldwide comes up in Igbogbo, Lagos State from Sunday, January 30 to Tuesday, February 1, 2022. The theme of this year’s Conference is: ‘Lord’s Or­dained Peace’ – Isaiah 26: 12 According to the Gener­al Secretary (Administra­tion), Bro. Ayo Bada, about 500 delegates from church­es under the Mission in Nigeria and Republic of Benin, were expected to at­tend this year’s conference. Rep Commends Akeredolu’s Commitment To Security In Ondo Another Two Killed In Serial Herders’ Attack On Benue Community He said the secretariat of the organisation would move to Igbogbo on Thurs­day, January 27 while other officers were expected to arrive on Saturday, Janu­ary 29. The Special Guest of Honour at the conference would be the governor of Lagos State, Mr. Babajide Olusola Sanwo-Olu. Highlights of the confer­ence would be the election of a new Lay President, consecration of new Bish­ops for the organisation as well as commissioning and elevation of other minis­ters on Sunday, January 30. The conference proper would hold on Monday, January 31, while the Women Fellowship would close the event on Tuesday, February 1 with its meet­ing.